-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/ds-smith-hires-lazard-to-handle-spicers-sale-sunday-times-says.html
DS Smith Plc (SMDS)  hired investment bank
 Lazard Ltd. (LAZ)  to handle the sale of Spicers, its office supplies
unit, the Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The sale would be worth 150 million pounds ($246 million),
according to the newspaper. DS Smith, which declined to comment,
has not yet made a final decision to sell the stationary
business, the newspaper reported, citing unidentified sources.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
